6:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-12","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Rate Mechanics"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Gate.io calculates funding every 8 hours using premium/discount to spot index, providing stability but fewer arbitrage opportunities. Drift's 1-hour funding cycles with vAMM pricing create more frequent rate resets and potential arbitrage windows. Gate.io's rates typically range ±0.01-0.1% per interval, while Drift's shorter cycles can show higher volatility. The DEX model means Drift rates respond faster to market imbalances but with less predictable patterns than Gate.io's established mechanism."}]]}]
7:["$","$Lb",null,{"items":[{"question":"Which exchange offers better funding rate arbitrage opportunities?","answer":"Gate.io provides more stable opportunities across 1,700+ pairs with predictable 8-hour cycles. Drift offers higher frequency opportunities with 1-hour funding but requires managing Solana network risks and lower liquidity."},{"question":"How do the funding calculation methods differ between platforms?","answer":"Gate.io uses traditional premium/discount calculations against spot indices every 8 hours. Drift employs a vAMM system with DLOB hybrid pricing, updating funding hourly based on virtual AMM imbalances and JIT liquidity."},{"question":"What are the main operational differences for arbitrage trading?","answer":"Gate.io requires traditional CEX account setup with KYC and offers fiat onramps. Drift operates on Solana requiring wallet connections, SOL for fees, and understanding of DeFi mechanics like liquidation thresholds."},{"question":"Which platform has more predictable funding rate patterns?","answer":"Gate.io's 8-hour intervals and established calculation methods provide more predictable funding patterns. Drift's hourly updates and vAMM mechanics create more volatile but potentially profitable short-term opportunities."}]}]
